Boil a #pot{} of water with @salt{¼%tsp} for your pasta. Peel and cut the @onion{½} in half lengthways through the root. Very thinly slice the onion into half moons.

Peel and crush (but don't chop) the @garlic clove{1}. Grate the @parmesan cheese{2}.

Cook the @bucatini pasta{200%g} in the boiling water for around ~{10%minutes} or until 'al dente'.

> 'Al dente' means the pasta is cooked but has a hint of firmness left in the middle.

Reserve a few tbsp of the pasta water and then drain the pasta when it's done.

In the meantime, heat @extra virgin olive oil{1%tbsp} in a pan on medium-low heat. Once hot, add the whole, crushed clove of garlic, the @chilli flakes{½} and the onion.

Cook for ~{5%minutes} before adding the @British smoked bacon lardons{⅓}. Cook the pancetta for a few mins until it is slightly crispy around the edges.

Add the @chopped tomatoes{1} to the pan with @salt{¼%tsp} and @sugar{¼%tsp} (if you have some). Add the @black olives{1} to the pan.

Season with plenty of freshly ground @black pepper{} and bubble away for ~{5%minutes} until the water has gone from the tomatoes and you have a nice, thick sauce.

Once the pasta is drained, add it to the sauce and toss the pan. Add the reserved pasta water to loosen up.

> Tossing pasta in tomato sauce can get a little messy, so take appropriate precautions!

Stir in the parmesan and serve immediately!